In reading through the documentation, I see no options for how a Confluence Task (with or without assignee, but with a due date) can be represented on a team calendar.  An Event Type should also factor in a Confluence Task.  If it has an assignee, it should be placed on their personal calendar as well as the team calendar for the space that it covers.  If it doesn't have an assignee, it should remain on the team calendar for that space.

While tasks don't have a start date, they are nonetheless "Events" that expect to be represented.  If  JIRA "Task" can be integrated into the calendar, the Confluence Task should be as well.

